SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 71
BY SENATOR SEABAUGH
A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
To commend and congratulate Kathy Holloway upon receiving the 2026 Dave Dixon
Louisiana Sports Leadership Award and on being inducted into the 2026 class of the
Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame.
WHEREAS, each year the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame in Natchitoches, Louisiana,
each year collaborates with the Louisiana Sports Writers Association in selecting a limited
number of sports figures who embody the character, skill, and talent worthy of being named
to the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame; and
WHEREAS, the Dave Dixon Louisiana Sports Leadership Award is a prestigious
honor presented annually by the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame to an individual who has
played a decisive role as a sports leader or administrator benefitting Louisiana and has
brought credit to Louisiana on the national and international stage; and
WHEREAS, Kathy Holloway has been selected for the 2026 Dave Dixon Louisiana
Sports Leadership Award from the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame and inducted into the 2026
Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame Induction Class; and
WHEREAS, Kathy Holloway is the fourth woman recipient of the Dave Dixon
Louisiana Sports Leadership Award; and
WHEREAS, Kathy Stewart Holloway, a native of Alexandria, Louisiana, has
dedicated her life to advancing education-based athletics and mentoring generations of
student-athletes; and
WHEREAS, Kathy Holloway has achieved historic distinction as the first female
